    Title: Vinava-Pitaka, Mahàvagga
    Locus: VIII 15
Tags:
  - Beauty-Peace=The Surface Of The Waters=Dominating the Waters
---
Said Visâkhâ the mother of Migâra： ‘Most wonderful, most marvellous is the
might and the power of the Tathâgata, in that though the floods are rolling on
knee-deep, and though the floods are rolling on waist-deep, yet is not a single
Bhikkhu wet, as to his feet or as to his robes.’
